      "content": "Many urban planners view congestion pricing as an almost inevitable and necessary tool for achieving aggressive climate goals. They see it as economically incentivizing the shift towards public transit and low-emission vehicles. Nevertheless, the pushback remains significant, as critics frame it as a tax that penalizes car dependency rather than solving the underlying infrastructure issues. Therefore, while the climate necessity is strong, the political and social opposition keeps its adoption process extremely controversial.",
